# 1. Purpose

This Functional Specification Document defines the functional behavior, system workflows, business rules, data requirements, notifications, and reporting capabilities required to implement an optimized dealership lead management solution using Salesforce Automotive Cloud.

This document serves as the primary reference for solution architects, developers, QA teams, and business stakeholders during implementation.

---

# 2. Solution Overview

The proposed solution will centralize dealership lead management activities within Salesforce Automotive Cloud.

The system will:

* Capture leads from multiple channels
* Validate customer information
* Assign leads automatically
* Support lead qualification workflows
* Schedule test drives
* Generate follow-up activities
* Convert qualified leads into opportunities
* Provide dashboards and management reports

---

# 3. Functional Modules

## Module 1: Lead Capture

### Description

The system shall capture customer inquiries received through various channels and create lead records in Salesforce.

### Supported Lead Sources

* Website Forms
* Showroom Visits
* Phone Calls
* Social Media Campaigns
* Referral Programs
* Marketing Events

### Functional Behavior

1. Customer inquiry received.
2. System validates required fields.
3. Lead record created automatically.
4. Lead status set to "New".
5. Assignment process initiated.

### Required Fields

| Field Name        | Type     | Mandatory |
| ----------------- | -------- | --------- |
| First Name        | Text     | Yes       |
| Last Name         | Text     | Yes       |
| Mobile Number     | Phone    | Yes       |
| Email Address     | Email    | Yes       |
| Preferred Vehicle | Picklist | No        |
| Lead Source       | Picklist | Yes       |
| Branch Location   | Picklist | Yes       |

### Validation Rules

* Email must be valid format.
* Phone number must contain 10 digits.
* Duplicate records must be checked before creation.

---

# Module 2: Lead Assignment

## Description

The system shall automatically assign leads to sales representatives based on predefined assignment rules.

## Assignment Logic

Priority Order:

1. Dealership Location
2. Vehicle Category
3. Sales Representative Availability
4. Round-Robin Assignment

## Functional Flow

1. Lead created.
2. System evaluates assignment criteria.
3. Representative selected.
4. Lead owner assigned.
5. Notification generated.

## Exception Handling

If no representative is available:

* Lead assigned to Sales Manager.
* Escalation notification generated.

---

# Module 3: Lead Qualification

## Description

The system shall support structured lead qualification activities.

## Qualification Criteria

| Criteria            | Description                                   |
| ------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Budget Availability | Customer has purchasing capacity              |
| Purchase Timeline   | Customer plans purchase within defined period |
| Vehicle Interest    | Customer identified preferred vehicle         |
| Contact Validation  | Communication established                     |

## Lead Status Values

* New
* Assigned
* Contacted
* Qualified
* Unqualified
* Nurturing
* Converted
* Closed

## Functional Flow

1. Representative contacts customer.
2. Customer information collected.
3. Qualification criteria evaluated.
4. Lead status updated.
5. Follow-up activity created.

---

# Module 4: Test Drive Management

## Description

The system shall allow dealership staff to schedule and manage customer test drives.

## Functional Flow

1. Qualified lead selected.
2. Vehicle selected.
3. Available time slot identified.
4. Appointment scheduled.
5. Confirmation notification sent.

## Appointment Information

| Field           | Description                   |
| --------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Customer Name   | Lead Name                     |
| Vehicle Model   | Selected Vehicle              |
| Test Drive Date | Scheduled Date                |
| Test Drive Time | Scheduled Time                |
| Branch Location | Assigned Dealership           |
| Status          | Scheduled/Completed/Cancelled |

## Notifications

* Confirmation Email
* SMS Reminder
* Sales Representative Alert

---

# Module 5: Opportunity Management

## Description

Qualified leads shall be converted into sales opportunities.

## Functional Flow

1. Lead marked as Qualified.
2. Representative initiates conversion.
3. System creates:

   * Account
   * Contact
   * Opportunity
4. Opportunity assigned to representative.
5. Opportunity enters sales pipeline.

## Opportunity Stages

* Qualification
* Vehicle Selection
* Negotiation
* Financing
* Proposal Submitted
* Closed Won
* Closed Lost

---

# Module 6: Follow-Up Management

## Description

The system shall automate customer follow-up activities.

## Functional Flow

1. Activity generated automatically.
2. Reminder sent to representative.
3. Customer contacted.
4. Outcome recorded.
5. Next action scheduled.

## Follow-Up Types

* Phone Call
* Email
* SMS
* Showroom Visit
* Test Drive Reminder

## Business Rules

* Every active lead must have at least one upcoming follow-up task.
* Overdue tasks trigger reminders.

---

# Module 7: Duplicate Management

## Description

The system shall prevent duplicate customer records.

## Duplicate Matching Criteria

| Field         | Match Rule  |
| ------------- | ----------- |
| Mobile Number | Exact Match |
| Email Address | Exact Match |

## System Behavior

If duplicate detected:

1. Warning displayed.
2. Existing record shown.
3. User decides:

   * Merge
   * Update Existing
   * Create New

